Package: PCA3Dviewer
Title: Interactive 3D PCA Viewer for 'genind' Data
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("James", "Hereward",
           email = "j.hereward@uq.edu.au",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-6468-6342")),
    person("Three.js Authors", role = c("ctb", "cph"),
           comment = "bundled three.js library (inst/js/three.min.js)"),
    person("James Hall", role = c("ctb", "cph"),
           comment = "bundled jsPDF library (inst/js/jspdf.umd.min.js)"))
Description: Runs a principal component analysis on a 'genind' object (from the
    'adegenet' package) and writes a single, self-contained HTML file with an
    interactive 3D scatter plot rendered with the bundled 'three.js' 'WebGL'
    library. The viewer supports selectable principal-component axes, a
    clickable population legend filter, a sample search box that highlights the
    matched sample with an arrow and label, a dark/light mode toggle,
    adjustable point size and opacity, switchable colour palettes, and image
    export to 'PNG' and (via the bundled 'jsPDF' library) 'PDF'. The generated
    file requires no internet access to view.
